",\"id\":\"msg_01U8hfistqgdVUHYEKZFBhzd\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01W7oSa1A5KqSwcWUdcxyN2N\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli/README.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2511,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":16291,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2511},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYjmeZTGa5TnERjZ3gSFN\",\"uuid\":\"4fbcab59-0e5e-4d99-a572-342eaaeec805\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"ac6eec0fc6ad11a59\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_014Zbzs22xZkbfXSZGaZbL3Y\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_016QE3mshzXCTyew8EMnepyc\",\"uuid\":\"5cf0f912-df47-42a4-98e7-3334a63a8ebc\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T10:24:42.595Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"5cf0f912-df47-42a4-98e7-3334a63a8ebc\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"03df2882-a2af-44d2-ad9e-d4dee3f44781\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"nodo/external-plugins\",\"slug\":\"kind-finding-toast\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01W7oSa1A5KqSwcWUdcxyN2N\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Entire CLI\\n     2→\\n     3→Entire hooks into your Git workflow to capture AI agent sessions as you work. Sessions are indexed alongside commits, creating a searchable record of how code was written in your repo.\\n     4→\\n     5→With Entire, you can:\\n     6→\\n     7→- **Understand why code changed** — see the full prompt/response transcript and files touched\\n     8→- **Recover instantly** — rewind to a known-good checkpoint when an agent goes sideways and resume seamlessly\\n     9→- **Keep Git history clean** — preserve agent context on a separate branch\\n    10→- **Onboard faster** — show the path from prompt → change → commit\\n    11→- **Maintain traceability** — support audit and compliance requirements when needed\\n    12→\\n    13→## Table of Contents\\n    14→\\n    15→- [Quick Start](#quick-start)\\n    16→- [Typical Workflow](#typical-workflow)\\n    17→- [Key Concepts](#key-concepts)\\n    18→  - [How It Works](#how-it-works)\\n    19→  - [Strategy](#strategy)\\n    20→- [Commands Reference](#commands-reference)\\n    21→- [Configuration](#configuration)\\n    22→- [Security & Privacy](#security--privacy)\\n    23→- [Troubleshooting](#troubleshooting)\\n    24→- [Development](#development)\\n    25→- [Getting Help](#getting-help)\\n    26→- [License](#license)\\n    27→\\n    28→## Requirements\\n    29→\\n    30→- Git\\n    31→- macOS or Linux (Windows via WSL)\\n    32→- [Claude Code](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code), [Gemini CLI](https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli), [OpenCode](https://opencode.ai/docs/cli/), or [Cursor](https://www.cursor.com/) installed and authenticated\\n    33→\\n    34→## Quick Start\\n    35→\\n    36→```bash\\n    37→# Install via Homebrew\\n    38→brew tap entireio/tap\\n    39→brew install entireio/tap/entire\\n    40→\\n    41→# Or install via Go\\n    42→go install github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire@latest\\n    43→\\n    44→# Enable in your project\\n    45→cd your-project && entire enable\\n    46→\\n    47→# Check status\\n    48→entire status\\n    49→```\\n    50→\\n    51→## Typical Workflow\\n    52→\\n    53→### 1. Enable Entire in Your Repository\\n    54→\\n    55→```\\n    56→entire enable\\n    57→```\\n    58→\\n    59→This installs agent and git hooks to work with your AI agent (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, or Cursor). You'll be prompted to select which agents to enable. To enable a specific agent non-interactively, use `entire enable --agent <name>` (e.g., `entire enable --agent cursor`).\\n    60→\\n    61→The hooks capture session data as you work. Checkpoints are created when you or the agent make a git commit. Your code commits stay clean, Entire never creates commits on your active branch. All session metadata is stored on a separate `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch.\\n    62→\\n    63→### 2. Work with Your AI Agent\\n    64→\\n    65→Just use Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, or Cursor normally. Entire runs in the background, tracking your session:\\n    66→\\n    67→```\\n    68→entire status  # Check current session status anytime\\n    69→```\\n    70→\\n    71→### 3. Rewind to a Previous Checkpoint\\n    72→\\n    73→If you want to undo some changes and go back to an earlier checkpoint:\\n    74→\\n    75→```\\n    76→entire rewind\\n    77→```\\n    78→\\n    79→This shows all available checkpoints in the current session. Select one to restore your code to that exact state.\\n    80→\\n    81→### 4. Resume a Previous Session\\n    82→\\n    83→To restore the latest checkpointed session metadata for a branch:\\n    84→\\n    85→```\\n    86→entire resume <branch>\\n    87→```\\n    88→\\n    89→Entire checks out the branch, restores the latest checkpointed session metadata (one or more sessions), and prints command(s) to continue.\\n    90→\\n    91→### 5. Disable Entire (Optional)\\n    92→\\n    93→```\\n    94→entire disable\\n    95→```\\n    96→\\n    97→Removes the git hooks. Your code and commit history remain untouched.\\n    98→\\n    99→## Key Concepts\\n   100→\\n   101→### Sessions\\n   102→\\n   103→A **session** represents a complete interaction with your AI agent, from start to finish. Each session captures all prompts, responses, files modified, and timestamps.\\n   104→\\n   105→**Session ID format:** `YYYY-MM-DD-<UUID>` (e.g., `2026-01-08-abc123de-f456-7890-abcd-ef1234567890`)\\n   106→\\n   107→Sessions are stored separately from your code commits on the `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch.\\n   108→\\n   109→### Checkpoints\\n   110→\\n   111→A **checkpoint** is a snapshot within a session that you can rewind to—a \\\"save point\\\" in your work.\\n   112→\\n   113→Checkpoints are created when you or the agent make a git commit. **Checkpoint IDs** are 12-character hex strings (e.g., `a3b2c4d5e6f7`).\\n   114→\\n   115→### How It Works\\n   116→\\n   117→```\\n   118→Your Branch                    entire/checkpoints/v1\\n   119→     │                                  │\\n   120→     ▼                                  │\\n   121→[Base Commit]                           │\\n   122→     │                                  │\\n   123→     │  ┌─── Agent works ───┐           │\\n   124→     │  │  Step 1           │           │\\n   125→     │  │  Step 2           │           │\\n   126→     │  │  Step 3           │           │\\n   127→     │  └───────────────────┘           │\\n   128→     │                                  │\\n   129→     ▼                                  ▼\\n   130→[Your Commit] ─────────────────► [Session Metadata]\\n   131→     │                           (transcript, prompts,\\n   132→     │                            files touched)\\n   133→     ▼\\n   134→```\\n   135→\\n   136→Checkpoints are saved as you work. When you commit, session metadata is permanently stored on the `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch and linked to your commit.\\n   137→\\n   138→### Strategy\\n   139→\\n   140→Entire uses a manual-commit strategy that keeps your git history clean:\\n   141→\\n   142→- **No commits on your branch** — Entire never creates commits on the active branch\\n   143→- **Safe on any branch** — works on main, master, and feature branches alike\\n   144→- **Non-destructive rewind** — restore files from any checkpoint without altering commit history\\n   145→- **Metadata stored separately** — all session data lives on the `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\\n   146→\\n   147→### Git Worktrees\\n   148→\\n   149→Entire works seamlessly with [git worktrees](https://git-scm.com/docs/git-worktree). Each worktree has independent session tracking, so you can run multiple AI sessions in different worktrees without conflicts.\\n   150→\\n   151→### Concurrent Sessions\\n   152→\\n   153→Multiple AI sessions can run on the same commit. If you start a second session while another has uncommitted work, Entire warns you and tracks them separately. Both sessions' checkpoints are preserved and can be rewound independently.\\n   154→\\n   155→## Commands Reference\\n   156→\\n   157→| Command          | Description                                                                                       |\\n   158→| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n   159→| `entire clean`   | Clean up orphaned Entire data                                                                     |\\n   160→| `entire disable` | Remove Entire hooks from repository                                                               |\\n   161→| `entire doctor`  | Fix or clean up stuck sessions                                                                    |\\n   162→| `entire enable`  | Enable Entire in your repository                                                                  |\\n   163→| `entire explain` | Explain a session or commit                                                                       |\\n   164→| `entire reset`   | Delete the shadow branch and session state for the current HEAD commit                            |\\n   165→| `entire resume`  | Switch to a branch, restore latest checkpointed session metadata, and show command(s) to continue |\\n   166→| `entire rewind`  | Rewind to a previous checkpoint                                                                   |\\n   167→| `entire status`  | Show current session info                                                                         |\\n   168→| `entire version` | Show Entire CLI version                                                                           |\\n   169→\\n   170→### `entire enable` Flags\\n   171→\\n   172→| Flag                   | Description                                                           |\\n   173→| ---------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n   174→| `--agent <name>`       | AI agent to install hooks for: `claude-code`, `gemini`, `opencode`, or `cursor` |\\n   175→| `--force`, `-f`        | Force reinstall hooks (removes existing Entire hooks first)           |\\n   176→| `--local`              | Write settings to `settings.local.json` instead of `settings.json`    |\\n   177→| `--project`            | Write settings to `settings.json` even if it already exists           |\\n   178→| `--skip-push-sessions` | Disable automatic pushing of session logs on git push                 |\\n   179→| `--telemetry=false`    | Disable anonymous usage analytics                                     |\\n   180→\\n   181→**Examples:**\\n   182→\\n   183→```\\n   184→# Force reinstall hooks\\n   185→entire enable --force\\n   186→\\n   187→# Save settings locally (not committed to git)\\n   188→entire enable --local\\n   189→```\\n   190→\\n   191→## Configuration\\n   192→\\n   193→Entire uses two configuration files in the `.entire/` directory:\\n   194→\\n   195→### settings.json (Project Settings)\\n   196→\\n   197→Shared across the team, typically committed to git:\\n   198→\\n   199→```json\\n   200→{\\n   201→  \\\"enabled\\\": true\\n   202→}\\n   203→```\\n   204→\\n   205→### settings.local.json (Local Settings)\\n   206→\\n   207→Personal overrides, gitignored by default:\\n   208→\\n   209→```json\\n   210→{\\n   211→  \\\"enabled\\\": false,\\n   212→  \\\"log_level\\\": \\\"debug\\\"\\n   213→}\\n   214→```\\n   215→\\n   216→### Configuration Options\\n   217→\\n   218→| Option                               | Values                           | Description                                          |\\n   219→| ------------------------------------ | -------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |\\n   220→| `enabled`                            | `true`, `false`                  | Enable/disable Entire                                |\\n   221→| `log_level`                          | `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `error` | Logging verbosity                                    |\\n   222→| `strategy_options.push_sessions`     | `true`, `false`                  | Auto-push `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch on git push |\\n   223→| `strategy_options.summarize.enabled` | `true`, `false`                  | Auto-generate AI summaries at commit time            |\\n   224→| `telemetry`                          | `true`, `false`                  | Send anonymous usage statistics to Posthog           |\\n   225→\\n   226→### Agent Hook Configuration\\n   227→\\n   228→Each agent stores its hook configuration in its own directory. When you run `entire enable`, hooks are installed in the appropriate location for each selected agent:\\n   229→\\n   230→| Agent       | Hook Location                 | Format            |\\n   231→|-------------| ----------------------------- | ----------------- |\\n   232→| Claude Code | `.claude/settings.json`       | JSON hooks config |\\n   233→| Gemini CLI  | `.gemini/settings.json`       | JSON hooks config |\\n   234→| OpenCode    | `.opencode/plugins/entire.ts` | TypeScript plugin |\\n   235→| Cursor  | `.cursor/hooks.json`          | JSON hooks config |\\n   236→\\n   237→You can enable multiple agents at the same time — each agent's hooks are independent. Entire detects which agents are active by checking for installed hooks, not by a setting in `settings.json`.\\n   238→\\n   239→### Auto-Summarization\\n   240→\\n   241→When enabled, Entire automatically generates AI summaries for checkpoints at commit time. Summaries capture intent, outcome, learnings, friction points, and open items from the session.\\n   242→\\n   243→```json\\n   244→{\\n   245→  \\\"strategy_options\\\": {\\n   246→    \\\"summarize\\\": {\\n   247→      \\\"enabled\\\": true\\n   248→    }\\n   249→  }\\n   250→}\\n   251→```\\n   252→\\n   253→**Requirements:**\\n   254→\\n   255→- Claude CLI must be installed and authenticated (`claude` command available in PATH)\\n   256→- Summary generation is non-blocking: failures are logged but don't prevent commits\\n   257→\\n   258→**Note:** Currently uses Claude CLI for summary generation. Other AI backends may be supported in future versions.\\n   259→\\n   260→### Settings Priority\\n   261→\\n   262→Local settings override project settings field-by-field. When you run `entire status`, it shows both project and local (effective) settings.\\n   263→\\n   264→### Gemini CLI\\n   265→\\n   266→Gemini CLI support is currently in preview. Entire can work with [Gemini CLI](https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli) as an alternative to Claude Code, or alongside it — you can have multiple agents' hooks enabled at the same time.\\n   267→\\n   268→To enable:\\n   269→\\n   270→```bash\\n   271→entire enable --agent gemini\\n   272→```\\n   273→\\n   274→All commands (`rewind`, `status`, `doctor`, etc.) work the same regardless of which agent is configured.\\n   275→\\n   276→If you run into any issues with Gemini CLI integration, please [open an issue](https://github.com/entireio/cli/issues).\\n   277→\\n   278→### OpenCode\\n   279→\\n   280→OpenCode support is currently in preview. Entire can work with [OpenCode](https://opencode.ai/docs/cli/) as an alternative to Claude Code, or alongside it — you can have multiple agents' hooks enabled at the same time.\\n   281→\\n   282→To enable:\\n   283→\\n   284→```bash\\n   285→entire enable --agent opencode\\n   286→```\\n   287→\\n   288→Or select OpenCode from the interactive agent picker when running `entire enable`.\\n   289→\\n   290→All commands (`rewind`, `status`, `doctor`, etc.) work the same regardless of which agent is configured.\\n   291→\\n   292→If you run into any issues with OpenCode integration, please [open an issue](https://github.com/entireio/cli/issues).\\n   293→\\n   294→### Cursor\\n   295→\\n   296→Cursor support is currently in preview. Entire can work with [Cursor](https://www.cursor.com/) as an alternative to Claude Code, or alongside it — you can have multiple agents' hooks enabled at the same time.\\n   297→\\n   298→Entire supports Cursor IDE and Cursor Agent CLI tool.\\n   299→\\n   300→To enable:\\n   301→\\n   302→```bash\\n   303→entire enable --agent cursor\\n   304→```\\n   305→\\n   306→Or select Cursor IDE from the interactive agent picker when running `entire enable`.\\n   307→\\n   308→Rewind is not available at this time, but other commands (`doctor`, `status` etc.) work the same as all other agents.\\n   309→\\n   310→If you run into any issues with Cursor integration, please [open an issue](https://github.com/entireio/cli/issues).\\n   311→\\n   312→## Security & Privacy\\n   313→\\n   314→**Your session transcripts are stored in your git repository** on the `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch. If your repository is public, this data is visible to anyone.\\n   315→\\n   316→Entire automatically redacts detected secrets (API keys, tokens, credentials) when writing to `entire/checkpoints/v1`, but redaction is best-effort. Temporary shadow branches used during a session may contain unredacted data and should not be pushed. See [docs/security-and-privacy.md](docs/security-and-privacy.md) for details.\\n   317→\\n   318→## Troubleshooting\\n   319→\\n   320→### Common Issues\\n   321→\\n   322→| Issue                    | Solution                                                |\\n   323→| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |\\n   324→| \\\"Not a git repository\\\"   | Navigate to a Git repository first                      |\\n   325→| \\\"Entire is disabled\\\"     | Run `entire enable`                                     |\\n   326→| \\\"No rewind points found\\\" | Work with your configured agent and commit your changes |\\n   327→| \\\"shadow branch conflict\\\" | Run `entire reset --force`                              |\\n   328→\\n   329→### SSH Authentication Errors\\n   330→\\n   331→If you see an error like this when running `entire resume`:\\n   332→\\n   333→```\\n   334→Failed to fetch metadata: failed to fetch entire/checkpoints/v1 from origin: ssh: handshake failed: ssh: unable to authenticate, attempted methods [none publickey], no supported methods remain\\n   335→```\\n   336→\\n   337→This is a [known issue with go-git's SSH handling](https://github.com/go-git/go-git/issues/411). Fix it by adding GitHub's host keys to your known_hosts file:\\n   338→\\n   339→```\\n   340→ssh-keyscan -t rsa github.com >> ~/.ssh/known_hosts\\n   341→ssh-keyscan -t ecdsa github.com >> ~/.ssh/known_hosts\\n   342→```\\n   343→\\n   344→### Debug Mode\\n   345→\\n   346→```\\n   347→# Via environment variable\\n   348→ENTIRE_LOG_LEVEL=debug entire status\\n   349→\\n   350→# Or via settings.local.json\\n   351→{\\n   352→  \\\"log_level\\\": \\\"debug\\\"\\n   353→}\\n   354→```\\n   355→\\n   356→### Resetting State\\n   357→\\n   358→```\\n   359→# Reset shadow branch for current commit\\n   360→entire reset --force\\n   361→\\n   362→# Disable and re-enable\\n   363→entire disable && entire enable --force\\n   364→```\\n   365→\\n   366→### Accessibility\\n   367→\\n   368→For screen reader users, enable accessible mode:\\n   369→\\n   370→```\\n   371→export ACCESSIBLE=1\\n   372→entire enable\\n   373→```\\n   374→\\n   375→This uses simpler text prompts instead of interactive TUI elements.\\n   376→\\n   377→## Development\\n   378→\\n   379→This project uses [mise](https://mise.jdx.dev/) for task automation and dependency management.\\n   380→\\n   381→### Prerequisites\\n   382→\\n   383→- [mise](https://mise.jdx.dev/) - Install with `curl https://mise.run | sh`\\n   384→\\n   385→### Getting Started\\n   386→\\n   387→```\\n   388→# Clone the repository\\n   389→git clone <repo-url>\\n   390→cd cli\\n   391→\\n   392→# Install dependencies (including Go)\\n   393→mise install\\n   394→\\n   395→# Trust the mise configuration (required on first setup)\\n   396→mise trust\\n   397→\\n   398→# Build the CLI\\n   399→mise run build\\n   400→```\\n   401→\\n   402→### Common Tasks\\n   403→\\n   404→```\\n   405→# Run tests\\n   406→mise run test\\n   407→\\n   408→# Run integration tests\\n   409→mise run test:integration\\n   410→\\n   411→# Run all tests (unit + integration, CI mode)\\n   412→mise run test:ci\\n   413→\\n   414→# Lint the code\\n   415→mise run lint\\n   416→\\n   417→# Format the code\\n   418→mise run fmt\\n   419→```\\n   420→\\n   421→## Getting Help\\n   422→\\n   423→```\\n   424→entire --help              # General help\\n   425→entire <command> --help    # Command-specific help\\n   426→```\\n   427→\\n   428→- **GitHub Issues:** Report bugs or request features at https://github.com/entireio/cli/issues\\n   429→- **Contributing:** See [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md) for guidelines\\n   430→\\n   431→## License\\n   432→\\n   433→MIT License - see [LICENSE](LICENSE) for details.\\n   434→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"da5b0a10-eea9-4745-9a7b-bdbdc431f2c4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T10:24:42.609Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"ac6eec0fc6ad11a59\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_014Zbzs22xZkbfXSZGaZbL3Y\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_016QE3mshzXCTyew8EMnepyc\",\"uuid\":\"626ea21c-57ba-4109-92fb-27c5c072f7e1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T10:24:42.612Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"626ea21c-57ba-4109-92fb-27c5c072f7e1\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"03df2882-a2af-44d2-ad9e-d4dee3f44781\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"nodo/external-plugins\",\"slug\":\"kind-finding