e\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# External Agent Plugin Protocol\\n     2→\\n     3→## Overview\\n     4→\\n     5→The Entire CLI supports external agent plugins — standalone binaries that implement the Agent interface via a subcommand-based protocol over stdin/stdout. This allows third-party agents to integrate with the CLI without modifying the main repository.\\n     6→\\n     7→## Discovery\\n     8→\\n     9→The CLI discovers external agents by scanning `$PATH` for executables matching the pattern `entire-agent-<name>`. For example, `entire-agent-cursor` would register as the \\\"cursor\\\" agent.\\n    10→\\n    11→- Binaries whose `<name>` conflicts with an already-registered built-in agent are skipped.\\n    12→- Discovery runs once during CLI initialization (before building the hooks command tree).\\n    13→- The binary must be executable and respond to the `info` subcommand.\\n    14→\\n    15→## Environment\\n    16→\\n    17→Every subcommand invocation sets:\\n    18→\\n    19→| Variable | Description |\\n    20→|---|---|\\n    21→| `ENTIRE_REPO_ROOT` | Absolute path to the git repository root |\\n    22→| `ENTIRE_PROTOCOL_VERSION` | Protocol version (`1`) |\\n    23→\\n    24→The working directory is set to the repository root.\\n    25→\\n    26→## Communication Model\\n    27→\\n    28→- **Subcommand-based:** Each Agent interface method maps to a CLI subcommand.\\n    29→- **JSON over stdin/stdout:** Structured data uses JSON. Transcripts use raw bytes.\\n    30→- **Stateless:** Each invocation is independent — no persistent connection.\\n    31→- **Exit codes:** `0` = success, non-zero = error. Error messages go to stderr.\\n    32→\\n    33→## Subcommands\\n    34→\\n    35→### Always Required\\n    36→\\n    37→#### `info`\\n    38→\\n    39→Returns agent metadata and declared capabilities.\\n    40→\\n    41→**Arguments:** None\\n    42→\\n    43→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n    44→\\n    45→```json\\n    46→{\\n    47→  \\\"protocol_version\\\": 1,\\n    48→  \\\"name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n    49→  \\\"type\\\": \\\"Cursor\\\",\\n    50→  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Cursor - AI-powered code editor\\\",\\n    51→  \\\"is_preview\\\": true,\\n    52→  \\\"protected_dirs\\\": [\\\".cursor\\\"],\\n    53→  \\\"hook_names\\\": [\\\"session-start\\\", \\\"session-end\\\", \\\"stop\\\"],\\n    54→  \\\"capabilities\\\": {\\n    55→    \\\"hooks\\\": true,\\n    56→    \\\"transcript_analyzer\\\": true,\\n    57→    \\\"transcript_preparer\\\": false,\\n    58→    \\\"token_calculator\\\": false,\\n    59→    \\\"text_generator\\\": false,\\n    60→    \\\"hook_response_writer\\\": false,\\n    61→    \\\"subagent_aware_extractor\\\": false\\n    62→  }\\n    63→}\\n    64→```\\n    65→\\n    66→The `capabilities` object determines which optional subcommands the CLI will call. If a capability is `false` or missing, the CLI will never invoke the corresponding subcommands.\\n    67→\\n    68→#### `detect`\\n    69→\\n    70→Checks whether the agent is present/usable in the current environment.\\n    71→\\n    72→**Arguments:** None\\n    73→\\n    74→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n    75→\\n    76→```json\\n    77→{\\\"present\\\": true}\\n    78→```\\n    79→\\n    80→#### `get-session-id`\\n    81→\\n    82→Extracts the session ID from a hook input event.\\n    83→\\n    84→**Input (stdin):** JSON — the [HookInput object](#hookinput-object)\\n    85→\\n    86→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n    87→\\n    88→```json\\n    89→{\\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\"}\\n    90→```\\n    91→\\n    92→#### `get-session-dir --repo-path <path>`\\n    93→\\n    94→Returns the directory where agent sessions are stored.\\n    95→\\n    96→**Arguments:**\\n    97→- `--repo-path` — Absolute path to the repository\\n    98→\\n    99→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   100→\\n   101→```json\\n   102→{\\\"session_dir\\\": \\\"/path/to/sessions\\\"}\\n   103→```\\n   104→\\n   105→#### `resolve-session-file --session-dir <dir> --session-id <id>`\\n   106→\\n   107→Resolves the session file path from a session directory and ID.\\n   108→\\n   109→**Arguments:**\\n   110→- `--session-dir` — Session directory path\\n   111→- `--session-id` — Session identifier\\n   112→\\n   113→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   114→\\n   115→```json\\n   116→{\\\"session_file\\\": \\\"/path/to/session/file.jsonl\\\"}\\n   117→```\\n   118→\\n   119→#### `read-session`\\n   120→\\n   121→Reads session data from a hook input event.\\n   122→\\n   123→**Input (stdin):** JSON — the [HookInput object](#hookinput-object)\\n   124→\\n   125→**Output (stdout):** JSON — [AgentSession object](#agentsession-object)\\n   126→\\n   127→```json\\n   128→{\\n   129→  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n   130→  \\\"agent_name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n   131→  \\\"repo_path\\\": \\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\n   132→  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/file.jsonl\\\",\\n   133→  \\\"start_time\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\",\\n   134→  \\\"native_data\\\": null,\\n   135→  \\\"modified_files\\\": [\\\"src/main.go\\\"],\\n   136→  \\\"new_files\\\": [],\\n   137→  \\\"deleted_files\\\": []\\n   138→}\\n   139→```\\n   140→\\n   141→#### `write-session`\\n   142→\\n   143→Writes/updates session data.\\n   144→\\n   145→**Input (stdin):** JSON — the [AgentSession object](#agentsession-object)\\n   146→\\n   147→**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n   148→\\n   149→#### `read-transcript --session-ref <path>`\\n   150→\\n   151→Reads a transcript file and returns its raw bytes.\\n   152→\\n   153→**Arguments:**\\n   154→- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n   155→\\n   156→**Output (stdout):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n   157→\\n   158→#### `chunk-transcript --max-size <n>`\\n   159→\\n   160→Splits a transcript into chunks for storage.\\n   161→\\n   162→**Input (stdin):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n   163→\\n   164→**Arguments:**\\n   165→- `--max-size` — Maximum chunk size in bytes\\n   166→\\n   167→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   168→\\n   169→```json\\n   170→{\\\"chunks\\\": [\\\"<base64-encoded-chunk>\\\", \\\"...\\\"]}\\n   171→```\\n   172→\\n   173→#### `reassemble-transcript`\\n   174→\\n   175→Reassembles transcript chunks back into a full transcript.\\n   176→\\n   177→**Input (stdin):** JSON\\n   178→\\n   179→```json\\n   180→{\\\"chunks\\\": [\\\"<base64-encoded-chunk>\\\", \\\"...\\\"]}\\n   181→```\\n   182→\\n   183→**Output (stdout):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n   184→\\n   185→#### `format-resume-command --session-id <id>`\\n   186→\\n   187→Returns the command a user can run to resume a session.\\n   188→\\n   189→**Arguments:**\\n   190→- `--session-id` — Session identifier\\n   191→\\n   192→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   193→\\n   194→```json\\n   195→{\\\"command\\\": \\\"cursor --resume abc123\\\"}\\n   196→```\\n   197→\\n   198→### Capability: `hooks`\\n   199→\\n   200→These subcommands are required when `capabilities.hooks` is `true`.\\n   201→\\n   202→#### `parse-hook --hook <name>`\\n   203→\\n   204→Parses a raw agent hook payload into a structured event.\\n   205→\\n   206→**Arguments:**\\n   207→- `--hook` — Hook name (e.g., \\\"stop\\\", \\\"session-start\\\")\\n   208→\\n   209→**Input (stdin):** Raw agent hook payload bytes.\\n   210→\\n   211→**Output (stdout):** JSON — the parsed [Event object](#event-object), or `null` if the payload is not relevant.\\n   212→\\n   213→#### `install-hooks [--local-dev] [--force]`\\n   214→\\n   215→Installs agent hooks for Entire integration.\\n   216→\\n   217→**Arguments:**\\n   218→- `--local-dev` — Use local development binary path (optional)\\n   219→- `--force` — Overwrite existing hooks (optional)\\n   220→\\n   221→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   222→\\n   223→```json\\n   224→{\\\"hooks_installed\\\": 3}\\n   225→```\\n   226→\\n   227→#### `uninstall-hooks`\\n   228→\\n   229→Removes installed agent hooks.\\n   230→\\n   231→**Arguments:** None\\n   232→\\n   233→**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n   234→\\n   235→#### `are-hooks-installed`\\n   236→\\n   237→Checks whether hooks are currently installed.\\n   238→\\n   239→**Arguments:** None\\n   240→\\n   241→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   242→\\n   243→```json\\n   244→{\\\"installed\\\": true}\\n   245→```\\n   246→\\n   247→### Capability: `transcript_analyzer`\\n   248→\\n   249→Required when `capabilities.transcript_analyzer` is `true`.\\n   250→\\n   251→#### `get-transcript-position --path <path>`\\n   252→\\n   253→Returns the current byte position/size of a transcript file.\\n   254→\\n   255→**Arguments:**\\n   256→- `--path` — Path to the transcript file\\n   257→\\n   258→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   259→\\n   260→```json\\n   261→{\\\"position\\\": 12345}\\n   262→```\\n   263→\\n   264→#### `extract-modified-files --path <path> --offset <n>`\\n   265→\\n   266→Extracts the list of files modified by the agent from a transcript.\\n   267→\\n   268→**Arguments:**\\n   269→- `--path` — Path to the transcript file\\n   270→- `--offset` — Byte offset to start reading from\\n   271→\\n   272→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   273→\\n   274→```json\\n   275→{\\\"files\\\": [\\\"path/to/file1.go\\\", \\\"path/to/file2.go\\\"], \\\"current_position\\\": 12345}\\n   276→```\\n   277→\\n   278→The `current_position` field returns the transcript position after extraction, allowing the caller to resume from that point on subsequent calls.\\n   279→\\n   280→#### `extract-prompts --session-ref <path> --offset <n>`\\n   281→\\n   282→Extracts user prompts from a transcript.\\n   283→\\n   284→**Arguments:**\\n   285→- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n   286→- `--offset` — Byte offset to start reading from\\n   287→\\n   288→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   289→\\n   290→```json\\n   291→{\\\"prompts\\\": [\\\"first prompt text\\\", \\\"second prompt text\\\"]}\\n   292→```\\n   293→\\n   294→#### `extract-summary --session-ref <path>`\\n   295→\\n   296→Extracts an AI-generated summary from a transcript.\\n   297→\\n   298→**Arguments:**\\n   299→- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n   300→\\n   301→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   302→\\n   303→```json\\n   304→{\\\"summary\\\": \\\"Summary text here\\\", \\\"has_summary\\\": true}\\n   305→```\\n   306→\\n   307→### Capability: `transcript_preparer`\\n   308→\\n   309→Required when `capabilities.transcript_preparer` is `true`.\\n   310→\\n   311→#### `prepare-transcript --session-ref <path>`\\n   312→\\n   313→Prepares/processes a transcript file (e.g., converting from raw format).\\n   314→\\n   315→**Arguments:**\\n   316→- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n   317→\\n   318→**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n   319→\\n   320→### Capability: `token_calculator`\\n   321→\\n   322→Required when `capabilities.token_calculator` is `true`.\\n   323→\\n   324→#### `calculate-tokens --offset <n>`\\n   325→\\n   326→Calculates token usage from a transcript.\\n   327→\\n   328→**Input (stdin):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n   329→\\n   330→**Arguments:**\\n   331→- `--offset` — Byte offset to start calculating from\\n   332→\\n   333→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   334→\\n   335→```json\\n   336→{\\n   337→  \\\"input_tokens\\\": 1500,\\n   338→  \\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\": 0,\\n   339→  \\\"cache_read_tokens\\\": 200,\\n   340→  \\\"output_tokens\\\": 500,\\n   341→  \\\"api_call_count\\\": 3,\\n   342→  \\\"subagent_tokens\\\": null\\n   343→}\\n   344→```\\n   345→\\n   346→Only `input_tokens` and `output_tokens` are required. The optional fields (`cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, `api_call_count`) default to `0` if omitted. `subagent_tokens` is an optional nested object with the same structure, for agents that spawn subagents.\\n   347→\\n   348→### Capability: `text_generator`\\n   349→\\n   350→Required when `capabilities.text_generator` is `true`.\\n   351→\\n   352→#### `generate-text --model <model>`\\n   353→\\n   354→Generates text using the agent's underlying LLM.\\n   355→\\n   356→**Input (stdin):** Prompt text.\\n   357→\\n   358→**Arguments:**\\n   359→- `--model` — Model to use for generation\\n   360→\\n   361→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   362→\\n   363→```json\\n   364→{\\\"text\\\": \\\"Generated response text\\\"}\\n   365→```\\n   366→\\n   367→### Capability: `hook_response_writer`\\n   368→\\n   369→Required when `capabilities.hook_response_writer` is `true`.\\n   370→\\n   371→#### `write-hook-response --message <message>`\\n   372→\\n   373→Writes a message in the agent's native hook response format.\\n   374→\\n   375→**Arguments:**\\n   376→- `--message` — Message to write\\n   377→\\n   378→**Output (stdout):** Agent-native format bytes (e.g., JSONL for Claude Code).\\n   379→\\n   380→### Capability: `subagent_aware_extractor`\\n   381→\\n   382→Required when `capabilities.subagent_aware_extractor` is `true`.\\n   383→\\n   384→#### `extract-all-modified-files --offset <n> --subagents-dir <dir>`\\n   385→\\n   386→Extracts modified files from both the main transcript and any subagent transcripts.\\n   387→\\n   388→**Input (stdin):** Raw main transcript bytes.\\n   389→\\n   390→**Arguments:**\\n   391→- `--offset` — Byte offset for the main transcript\\n   392→- `--subagents-dir` — Directory containing subagent transcripts\\n   393→\\n   394→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   395→\\n   396→```json\\n   397→{\\\"files\\\": [\\\"file1.go\\\", \\\"file2.go\\\"]}\\n   398→```\\n   399→\\n   400→#### `calculate-total-tokens --offset <n> --subagents-dir <dir>`\\n   401→\\n   402→Calculates total token usage across main transcript and subagent transcripts.\\n   403→\\n   404→**Input (stdin):** Raw main transcript bytes.\\n   405→\\n   406→**Arguments:**\\n   407→- `--offset` — Byte offset for the main transcript\\n   408→- `--subagents-dir` — Directory containing subagent transcripts\\n   409→\\n   410→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   411→\\n   412→```json\\n   413→{\\n   414→  \\\"input_tokens\\\": 5000,\\n   415→  \\\"cache_creation_tokens\\\": 0,\\n   416→  \\\"cache_read_tokens\\\": 1000,\\n   417→  \\\"output_tokens\\\": 2000,\\n   418→  \\\"api_call_count\\\": 8,\\n   419→  \\\"subagent_tokens\\\": {\\n   420→    \\\"input_tokens\\\": 2000,\\n   421→    \\\"output_tokens\\\": 800\\n   422→  }\\n   423→}\\n   424→```\\n   425→\\n   426→Same token usage format as `calculate-tokens`. The `subagent_tokens` field aggregates usage from all subagents.\\n   427→\\n   428→## Shared Object Definitions\\n   429→\\n   430→### HookInput Object\\n   431→\\n   432→The HookInput object is passed via stdin to `get-session-id` and `read-session`.\\n   433→\\n   434→```json\\n   435→{\\n   436→  \\\"hook_type\\\": \\\"stop\\\",\\n   437→  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n   438→  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/transcript.jsonl\\\",\\n   439→  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\",\\n   440→  \\\"user_prompt\\\": \\\"Fix the login bug\\\",\\n   441→  \\\"tool_name\\\": \\\"Write\\\",\\n   442→  \\\"tool_use_id\\\": \\\"toolu_abc123\\\",\\n   443→  \\\"tool_input\\\": {\\\"path\\\": \\\"/src/main.go\\\"},\\n   444→  \\\"raw_data\\\": {\\\"custom_field\\\": \\\"value\\\"}\\n   445→}\\n   446→```\\n   447→\\n   448→| Field | Type | Description |\\n   449→|---|---|---|\\n   450→| `hook_type` | string | Hook type: `session_start`, `session_end`, `user_prompt_submit`, `stop`, `pre_tool_use`, `post_tool_use` |\\n   451→| `session_id` | string | Agent session identifier |\\n   452→| `session_ref` | string | Agent-specific session reference (typically a file path) |\\n   453→| `timestamp` | string | RFC 3339 timestamp |\\n   454→| `user_prompt` | string | User's prompt text (from `user_prompt_submit` hooks). Optional. |\\n   455→| `tool_name` | string | Tool name (from `pre_tool_use`/`post_tool_use` hooks). Optional. |\\n   456→| `tool_use_id` | string | Tool invocation ID. Optional. |\\n   457→| `tool_input` | object | Raw tool input JSON. Optional. |\\n   458→| `raw_data` | object | Agent-specific data for extension. Optional. |\\n   459→\\n   460→### AgentSession Object\\n   461→\\n   462→Used as input to `write-session` and output from `read-session`.\\n   463→\\n   464→```json\\n   465→{\\n   466→  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n   467→  \\\"agent_name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n   468→  \\\"repo_path\\\": \\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\n   469→  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/transcript.jsonl\\\",\\n   470→  \\\"start_time\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\",\\n   471→  \\\"native_data\\\": null,\\n   472→  \\\"modified_files\\\": [\\\"src/main.go\\\"],\\n   473→  \\\"new_files\\\": [\\\"src/new_file.go\\\"],\\n   474→  \\\"deleted_files\\\": []\\n   475→}\\n   476→```\\n   477→\\n   478→| Field | Type | Description |\\n   479→|---|---|---|\\n   480→| `session_id` | string | Agent session identifier |\\n   481→| `agent_name` | string | Agent registry name |\\n   482→| `repo_path` | string | Absolute path to the repository |\\n   483→| `session_ref` | string | Path/reference to session in agent's storage |\\n   484→| `start_time` | string | RFC 3339 timestamp of session start |\\n   485→| `native_data` | bytes/null | Session content in agent's native format (opaque to CLI) |\\n   486→| `modified_files` | string[] | Files modified during the session |\\n   487→| `new_files` | string[] | Files created during the session |\\n   488→| `deleted_files` | string[] | Files deleted during the session |\\n   489→\\n   490→### Event Object\\n   491→\\n   492→Returned by `parse-hook`. Represents a normalized lifecycle event.\\n   493→\\n   494→```json\\n   495→{\\n   496→  \\\"type\\\": 3,\\n   497→  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n   498→  \\\"session_ref\\\": \\\"/path/to/transcript.jsonl\\\",\\n   499→  \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Fix the login bug\\\",\\n   500→  \\\"model\\\": \\\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\\\",\\n   501→  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-01-13T12:00:00Z\\\"\\n   502→}\\n   503→```\\n   504→\\n   505→| Field | Type | Description |\\n   506→|---|---|---|\\n   507→| `type` | int | **Required.** Event type (see table below) |\\n   508→| `session_id` | string | **Required.** Agent session identifier |\\n   509→| `previous_session_id` | string | Non-empty when this event represents a session continuation/handoff. Optional. |\\n   510→| `session_ref` | string | Agent-specific transcript reference. Optional. |\\n   511→| `prompt` | string | User's prompt text (on `TurnStart` events). Optional. |\\n   512→| `model` | string | LLM model identifier. Optional. |\\n   513→| `timestamp` | string | RFC 3339 timestamp. Optional. |\\n   514→| `tool_use_id` | string | Tool invocation ID (for `SubagentStart`/`SubagentEnd`). Optional. |\\n   515→| `subagent_id` | string | Subagent instance ID (for `SubagentEnd`). Optional. |\\n   516→| `tool_input` | object | Raw tool input JSON (for subagent type/description extraction). Optional. |\\n   517→| `subagent_type` | string | Kind of subagent (for `SubagentStart`/`SubagentEnd`). Optional. |\\n   518→| `task_description` | string | Subagent task description. Optional. |\\n   519→| `response_message` | string | Message to display to the user via the agent. Optional. |\\n   520→| `metadata` | object | Agent-specific state preserved across events. Optional. |\\n   521→\\n   522→**Event types:**\\n   523→\\n   524→| Value | Name | Description |\\n   525→|---|---|---|\\n   526→| 1 | SessionStart | Agent session has begun |\\n   527→| 2 | TurnStart | User submitted a prompt, agent is about to work |\\n   528→| 3 | TurnEnd | Agent finished responding to a prompt |\\n   529→| 4 | Compaction | Agent is compressing its context window (triggers save + offset reset) |\\n   530→| 5 | SessionEnd | Session has been terminated |\\n   531→| 6 | SubagentStart | A subagent (task) has been spawned |\\n   532→| 7 | SubagentEnd | A subagent (task) has completed |\\n   533→\\n   534→## Error Handling\\n   535→\\n   536→- Exit code `0` indicates success.\\n   537→- Any non-zero exit code indicates an error.\\n   538→- Error messages 