"slug\":\"kind-finding-toast\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T10:29:39.136Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01D2w78Z4JhTCKz4Xpp8FSUm\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_016VgUXCtWpwNLVRN7T3mQGV\",\"name\":\"Glob\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"review-*.md\",\"path\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":659,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":62993,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":659},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYjn2RRgk6kii7LZ3cXy2\",\"uuid\":\"3d00193d-d815-4d64-96bd-21021c80e8fd\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"ad5c9d8d6c2a4581b\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01UGbVEAacMxqeKWuhp8pFbZ\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01S6TniapzHM4wwEcRM3hsv5\",\"uuid\":\"543e71ae-0319-4c41-9401-314eb8798596\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T10:29:39.136Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"543e71ae-0319-4c41-9401-314eb8798596\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"03df2882-a2af-44d2-ad9e-d4dee3f44781\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"nodo/external-plugins\",\"slug\":\"kind-finding-toast\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_016VgUXCtWpwNLVRN7T3mQGV\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli/docs/requirements/external-plugins/review-01.md\\n/Users/nodo/work/cli/docs/requirements/external-plugins/review-02.md\"}]},\"uuid\":\"65192329-1028-4cd5-8b7e-aee939cd70d2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T10:29:39.465Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"ad5c9d8d6c2a4581b\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01UGbVEAacMxqeKWuhp8pFbZ\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01S6TniapzHM4wwEcRM3hsv5\",\"uuid\":\"a025a259-75e5-4269-a5b9-190e519560ad\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T10:29:39.466Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"a025a259-75e5-4269-a5b9-190e519560ad\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"03df2882-a2af-44d2-ad9e-d4dee3f44781\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"nodo/external-plugins\",\"slug\":\"kind-finding-toast\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T10:30:34.948Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_014FLRAvThqpPhd2MDB6aswJ\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01WmkYbJivS88ed3gNGHEoZR\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli/review-03.md\",\"content\":\"# Review 03\\n\\n> Status: pending-dev\\n> Date: 2026-03-05\\n> Reviewer: Code Review Agent\\n> Verdict: APPROVE\\n\\n## Previous Review Status\\n\\n### From review-01\\n- [x] Issue 1: Unbounded `io.ReadAll` in `ParseHookEvent` - FIXED (uses `io.LimitReader` with 10MB cap)\\n- [x] Issue 3: Many methods use `context.Background()` - ACKNOWLEDGED as interface limitation, acceptable\\n- [x] Issue 5: Agent name from filename not validated - STILL OUTSTANDING (low risk, see below)\\n- [x] Issue 6: `cmd.Environ()` inherits full parent environment - STILL OUTSTANDING (documentation gap, see below)\\n- [x] Issue 7: No stdout buffer size limit - FIXED (see below)\\n- [x] Issue 11: Unchecked `EventType` cast - MITIGATED (see below)\\n- [x] Issue 12: Silent empty-string returns with no logging - STILL OUTSTANDING (low risk)\\n- [x] Issue 13: Discovery runs on every hook invocation - FIXED (see below)\\n\\n### From review-02\\n- [x] Issue 1 (Critical): `DiscoverAndRegister` runs during command tree construction - FIXED. Discovery now happens lazily inside the `RunE` fallback of the hooks command (`hooks_cmd.go`:37-40), only triggered when an unknown subcommand is invoked (i.e., an external agent hook). Non-hook commands like `entire version` and `entire status` no longer pay the discovery cost.\\n- [x] Issue 2 (Critical): No stdout buffer limit - FIXED. The `run()` method now uses a `limitedWriter` wrapper (`external.go`:428-467) that caps both stdout and stderr at 10MB. The writer silently discards excess bytes without killing the process, which is the correct behavior.\\n- [ ] Issue 3: Agent name validation still missing - STILL OUTSTANDING (see Important item 1 below)\\n- [ ] Issue 4: Silent failures without logging in `GetSessionID`, `ResolveSessionFile`, `FormatResumeCommand` - STILL OUTSTANDING (see Suggestions item 1 below)\\n- [ ] Issue 5: `EventType` range not validated in `toEvent()` - MITIGATED (see below)\\n- [x] Issue 6: Mock script JSON injection fragility - ACKNOWLEDGED, low risk since test values are controlled\\n- [x] Issue 7: Discovery tests modify global registry - ACKNOWLEDGED, unique names prevent collisions\\n\\n## New Findings\\n\\n### Critical (Must Fix)\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n### Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n1. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/discovery.go`:55] Agent name from filename still not validated (carried from review-01 #5, review-02 #3)**\\n\\n   The agent name is derived directly from the binary filename with no validation:\\n   ```go\\n   agentName := types.AgentName(strings.TrimPrefix(name, binaryPrefix))\\n   ```\\n\\n   Edge cases remain: a binary named `entire-agent-` (empty suffix) produces an empty agent name; `entire-agent-foo bar` (with a space) produces `\\\"foo bar\\\"`. While unlikely on a real system, adding a simple regex check is minimal effort and eliminates an entire class of edge cases. This has been flagged in two prior reviews.\\n\\n   Suggested fix:\\n   ```go\\n   nameStr := strings.TrimPrefix(name, binaryPrefix)\\n   if nameStr == \\\"\\\" || !regexp.MustCompile(`^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$`).MatchString(nameStr) {\\n       continue\\n   }\\n   ```\\n\\n   Risk: Low. Impact: Low. Effort: ~10 minutes.\\n\\n### Suggestions (Consider)\\n\\n1. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external.go`:123-137, 151-161, 192-201] Add debug logging to silent failure paths**\\n\\n   `GetSessionID`, `ResolveSessionFile`, and `FormatResumeCommand` return empty strings on any error with no logging. External agent failures (process crashes, protocol mismatches, timeouts) are harder to debug than built-in agent failures. Adding `logging.Debug` calls would help operators diagnose issues without changing the interface contract. Carried from review-01 #12 and review-02 #4.\\n\\n2. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/types.go`:148-150] `EventType` validation in `toEvent()`**\\n\\n   The `ej.Type` integer is cast directly to `agent.EventType` without range checking. However, reviewing `DispatchLifecycleEvent` in `lifecycle.go`:53-54, the dispatcher has a `default` case that returns `fmt.Errorf(\\\"unknown lifecycle event type: %d\\\", event.Type)`. This means unknown event types are caught at dispatch time and produce a clear error. The risk is therefore low -- the error surfaces one layer later than ideal, but it does surface. Downgrading from review-02's \\\"Important\\\" to \\\"Suggestion.\\\"\\n\\n3. **[`docs/architecture/external-agent-protocol.md`:17-23] Document that external binaries inherit the full parent environment**\\n\\n   The protocol doc lists `ENTIRE_REPO_ROOT` and `ENTIRE_PROTOCOL_VERSION` but does not mention that the full parent environment is also passed. Plugin authors should be aware of this. A one-line note would suffice. Carried from review-01 #6 and review-02 #9.\\n\\n4. **[`cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external.go`:34-53] `New()` does not validate that `info.Name` matches the binary-derived name**\\n\\n   `DiscoverAndRegister` uses the binary filename to derive the agent name (`entire-agent-foo` -> `foo`), but `New()` stores whatever the binary returns in `info.Name`. If they differ, `agent.Name()` returns the `info.Name` value while the registry key is the filename-derived name. This could cause confusion in logs and `entire status` output. Consider documenting that the filename is the authoritative name, or validating they match. Carried from review-02 #10.\\n\\n### Praise\\n\\n- **Critical issues from review-02 are properly addressed.** The lazy discovery pattern is well-implemented -- external agents are only discovered when the hooks RunE fallback fires with an unrecognized agent name. The `limitedWriter` for stdout/stderr is a clean solution that silently caps output without killing the process.\\n\\n- **The `limitedWriter` implementation is correct.** It reports the full `len(p)` to the caller even when truncating, so the external process does not receive a short-write error and does not get killed by SIGPIPE. This is the right behavior for a safety cap.\\n\\n- **Lazy discovery is correctly scoped.** The `RunE` fallback at `hooks_cmd.go`:30-48 only fires when Cobra cannot match a built-in agent subcommand. Built-in agents are still registered eagerly at `hooks_cmd.go`:56-64 without any process spawning. This is an elegant split.\\n\\n- **Comprehensive test coverage.** Discovery tests cover 9 scenarios. External agent tests cover all subcommands, error paths, timeouts, and capability wrapping. Capability tests cover all 7 optional interfaces with declared/undeclared/not-implemented variants. The architecture test correctly excludes `external` from the self-registering agent check.\\n\\n- **Capability gating pattern remains excellent.** The `CapabilityDeclarer` + `As*` helper pattern is clean, type-safe, and backward-compatible with built-in agents. The compile-time interface checks at the bottom of `capabilities.go` are good practice.\\n\\n- **Protocol documentation is thorough.** `external-agent-protocol.md` is well-structured with complete coverage of all subcommands, shared types, and the discovery mechanism.\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\n**Overall assessment: APPROVE**\\n\\nBoth critical issues from review-02 have been properly fixed:\\n1. Discovery is now lazy -- only runs when an external agent hook is actually invoked via the RunE fallback.\\n2. Stdout/stderr from external binaries are capped at 10MB via `limitedWriter`.\\n\\nThe remaining open items are all low-risk improvements that can be addressed in follow-up work:\\n- Agent name validation from filename (easy fix, flagged since review-01)\\n- Debug logging in silent failure paths (quality-of-life for debugging)\\n- Protocol doc environment note (one-line addition)\\n- `info.Name` vs filename mismatch documentation\\n\\nNone of these block the merge. The feature is well-architected, thoroughly tested, and the security-critical issues (unbounded I/O, discovery timing) have been addressed.\\n\\n**Estimated effort for remaining suggestions:** ~1 hour total, can be done as follow-up.\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":177,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":63652,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":177},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYjn2jJDyyBW6DpD5r8F6\",\"uuid\":\"89207793-50c8-4e08-a213-e3eff4139238\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"ad5c9d8d6c2a4581b\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01UGbVEAacMxqeKWuhp8pFbZ\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01S6TniapzHM4wwEcRM3hsv5\",\"uuid\":\"4fe9fa5b-5758-4393-9e84-f28c278d8b0a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T10:30:34.948Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4fe9fa5b-5758-4393-9e84-f28c278d8b0a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"03df2882-a2af-44d2-ad9e-d4dee3f44781\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"nodo/external-plugins\",\"slug\":\"kind-finding-toast\",\"type\":\"progre